        <h2 id="evo-cyber-faq-h2">Frequently Asked Questions About Cyber Security in Perth</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="evo-faq__grid">
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What is cyber security for small businesses in Perth?</h4>
          <p>Small business cyber security means implementing the right combination of tools, processes and training to protect your business from ransomware, phishing, data breaches and BEC fraud. EvoTech Digital provides layered, affordable cyber security specifically designed for Perth SMBs — no enterprise-sized budget required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What is MDR and do Perth SMBs need it?</h4>
          <p>Managed Detection and Response (MDR) is a 24/7 cyber security service where expert analysts monitor your systems, hunt threats and respond to incidents in real time. Perth SMBs need MDR because attackers strike at all hours, AI-powered threats bypass standard antivirus, and most small businesses can't afford a full-time security team.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Is the Essential Eight mandatory for Perth businesses?</h4>
          <p>The Essential Eight is mandatory for Australian government entities and strongly recommended for all businesses. It is increasingly required by cyber insurers and enterprise clients. Currently 78% of Australian organisations haven't reached Maturity Level 2 — the baseline. EvoTech helps Perth businesses close this gap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>How much does a cyber security audit cost in Perth?</h4>
          <p>EvoTech Digital offers a free introductory cyber security health check and Essential Eight gap assessment for Perth businesses — no cost, no obligation. A full penetration test and comprehensive compliance audit is scoped and quoted based on your environment size. Contact us to get started.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What are the biggest cyber threats for Perth businesses in 2026?</h4>
          <p>The top threats for Perth SMBs in 2026 are AI-powered phishing, ransomware-as-a-service, business email compromise (BEC), supply chain attacks and credential theft. The ASD reports the average cost of a cyber incident for an Australian small business reached $56,600 in 2024-25 — making prevention far cheaper than recovery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Does my business need cyber insurance and how does it relate to security?</h4>
          <p>Cyber insurance is increasingly important for Perth businesses — but insurers are tightening requirements. Many now require evidence of MFA, endpoint protection, tested backups and Essential Eight progress before providing coverage or competitive premiums. EvoTech's security stack directly supports insurability and lower premiums.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Can you train our Perth staff on cyber security?</h4>
          <p>Yes. EvoTech Digital provides security awareness training including simulated phishing campaigns, interactive training modules, monthly progress reports and policy support. Training has been shown to reduce phishing click-through rates by over 85% within 90 days — making your team a powerful line of defence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>How quickly can EvoTech protect our Perth business?</h4>
          <p>Critical protections — MFA, email security, endpoint protection and dark web monitoring — can typically be deployed within 1–5 business days. Our onboarding is designed to deliver immediate risk reduction while broader Essential Eight compliance and MDR monitoring are configured in parallel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

